To find the intersection of sets A and B, we look for the elements that are common to both sets. In this case, the intersection is:

A ∩ B = {6}

To find the union of sets A and B, we combine all the elements from both sets, without repeating any elements. In this case, the union is:

A ∪ B = {2, 3, 4, 6, 8, 9, 10, 12}
